==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: oo
<hw>o"o</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hawaiian.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any of several beautiful birds of the genus
<gen>Moho</gen>, including the extinct <spn>Moho nobilis</spn>. They are
<isa>honey-eaters</isa> native to the Hawaiian Islands. It yields the
brilliant yellow feathers formerly used in making the royal robes.
Called also <altname>yellow-tufted honeysucker</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ooecium</ent>⟦br⟧
